 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rewrite digest and attention as the prioritized action queue","description":"Rewrite digest and attention so they form the heart of the ongoing operator loop rather than acting like separate vaguely-related summaries. This task exists because ntm's strongest agent-native idea is the attention feed, and the redesign should put that at the center.","design":"Digest should answer what changed since a cursor in grouped, replay-safe form, including correlated actuation outcomes, operator attention-state changes, and intentional resurfacing of previously cooled-down or snoozed issues. Attention should answer what deserves action now, with reason codes, freshness, severity, stable resource references, request or outcome correlation handles where relevant, structured next_actions or equivalent remediation descriptors, compact evidence summaries or explanation handles, explicit aggregation or suppression markers when items represent rolled-up churn rather than raw event volume, and clear indicators when an item is pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. The two surfaces should feel like adjacent views over the same durable state rather than unrelated features, and they should bridge cleanly into inspect and diagnostics flows when an operator needs to understand why an item is present or absent. This task is where ntm steals the derived-actionability lesson from vibe_cockpit without adopting its fleet or analytics posture.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when digest and attention are coherent, prioritized, cursor-aware surfaces that help an agent tend the system over time instead of repeatedly rescanning the entire world, while still supporting safe retries, verified outcomes, durable operator control, and a concise signal-to-noise ratio.","notes":"If agents still need to reconstruct the next action from raw dumps, the redesign has missed its main ergonomic payoff.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:17.499375794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:22.493690943Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:31.860408763Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:48.280017075Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:58.558445530Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:23.095867952Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:34.463848955Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:25.674213998Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:49.170632351Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:03.333815090Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:31.912454353Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:03.868060207Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:43.717946841Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:03.251061190Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:04.415158483Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:17.499375794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":353,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: digest and attention should preserve actionability while avoiding raw-secret churn. If an item depends on hidden evidence, the surface should carry safe previews, disclosure markers, and drill-down handles instead of dumping unsafe text.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:22Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for session and agent drill-down","description":"Rationalize the drill-down surfaces used after bootstrap and triage for session and agent inspection. This task exists because operators need to inspect panes, agents, output, activity, context, and process state in detail, but that detail should project from the shared model instead of recreating command sprawl.","design":"The work should decide which session and agent inspect views remain distinct commands or modes, how they key into sessions, agents, and panes, how invalid or stale lookup requests are reported with machine-actionable follow-up guidance, and how they expose detail that is too verbose for snapshot, status, or attention. It should also make explicit how output, activity, context, and process detail is presented without leaking raw tmux mechanics back into the surface contract, and where these views deliberately hand off to the shared diagnostics flow when deeper why, evidence, truncation, or replay context is needed.\n\nThe goal is disciplined drill-down for session and agent state, not a generic debug dump.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when session and agent inspect surfaces are coherently defined and backed by the shared runtime projection with stable keys, detail semantics, and user-facing purpose.","notes":"A useful heuristic: a session or agent inspect surface should answer a focused follow-up question raised by snapshot or attention, not replace them.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:18.455554982Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:32.748220036Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:59.118868718Z","created_by":